This paper deals with the problem of learning a kernel matrix from relative comparisons, which is a common task in machine learning and falls under the category of supervised learning. The use of auxiliary kernels to aid in the learning process is a common technique in machine learning and can be applied to various sub-fields such as natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The optimization formulation used in this paper is convex, which is a common technique in optimization and falls under the category of scientific computing (cs.SI). Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, and cs.SI.
